This paper discusses the performance of various bibliometric indicators in measuring impact, specifically in the biomedical area. While the paper does not focus on a specific computer science subfield, it does use bibliometric analysis which is commonly used in digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper discusses the normalization of citation impact across different fields (cs.CY), and the use of post-publication peer review systems (cs.SI) in assessing the quality of papers. Finally, the paper also touches on the use of citation scores (cs.CR) as a measure of impact.
